@title [markdown]You might imagine that this could lead a writer to draw so many connections to something that they became hard to choose between. However, connections to something can be grouped, which lets the number of connections to it stay small. This is just like managing a folder in a file tree: If a folder has too much stuff, you can divide it into subfolders, and it becomes easier to read.
